---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import siteData from '../data/site.json';

const page = siteData.pages.about;
const styles = [
  'assets/css/tokens.css',
  'assets/css/interior-base.css',
  'assets/css/layout.css',
  'assets/css/components.css',
  'assets/css/mission.css',
];
---
<Base
  title={page.title}
  description={page.description}
  canonical={page.canonical}
  subtitle={page.subtitle}
  eyebrow={page.eyebrow}
  introKicker={page.introKicker}
  introTitle={page.introTitle}
  introText={page.introText}
  currentNav={page.currentNav}
  styles={styles}
>
  <section class="card mission-copy lede-card">
    <p>Saint Expedite is the patron of urgent causes, the saint invoked when it cannot wait. The press takes his name and his economy: no institutional overhead, no board, no grants, no permissions required. We publish from New Orleans, outside the credentialing apparatus, in the conviction that Southern writing at its best has always operated past the approval systems that would contain it.</p>
    <p>Three active arms: SEXP for original fiction and novella, the Library of the Southern Civilization for Southern reprints and archival work, and a European translation series across Spanish, French, and Russian.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="form-trust" aria-label="Project phases">
    <div class="trust-card">
      <strong>Phase one — A presence</strong>
      The catalog, the channel, the first books. Direct to the reader. No institutional apparatus. Proof that something is here before building the next thing.
    </div>
    <div class="trust-card">
      <strong>Phase two — A magazine</strong>
      A print journal for fiction, reprints, translation, and criticism. No academic board. No corporate backing. No interest in being convenient. The kind of journal Southern letters does not currently have. Distributed directly, sustained by the catalog.
    </div>
    <div class="trust-card">
      <strong>Phase three — A fellowship</strong>
      A foundation mechanism for Southern writers outside the university and the grant system. Money, time, and recognition without the credentialing apparatus. Self-sustaining through the press's own economics. No committee. No application form.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card mission-copy">
    <p>Zero guardrails. Non-institutional. Post-corporate. The press operates past the approval structures of literary commerce. Not in opposition to them, because opposition still requires acknowledgment. Past them.</p>
  </section>

  <Fragment slot="scripts">
    <script is:inline src="/assets/js/site-shell.js" type="module"></script>
  </Fragment>
</Base>
